    "cluster.intro.body": {
      "comment": "Pip Count cluster",
      "extractionState": "manual",
      "localizations": {
        "de": {
          "stringUnit": {
            "state": "translated",
            "value": "Cluster Counting ist eine von Jack Kissane entwickelte Technik, mit der du Pip Counts deutlich schneller schätzt als mit der klassischen Punkt-für-Punkt-Methode. Statt jeden Stein einzeln zu multiplizieren, ordnest du die Steine gedanklich zu erkennbaren Mustern – Clustern –, deren Pip-Summen leicht zu berechnen sind. Mit etwas Übung zählst du die meisten Stellungen in wenigen Sekunden.\n\nDie zentrale Erkenntnis ist einfach: Zwei Punkte, die sich auf dem Brett spiegeln, ergeben zusammen 25. Punkt 1 und Punkt 24, Punkt 6 und Punkt 19, Punkt 12 und Punkt 13 – immer 25. Vier Steine in Spiegelpositionen zählen daher 50, egal wo genau sie stehen.\n\nStatt endlose Kombinationen auswendig zu lernen, hat Kissane sieben Referenzpositionen identifiziert, deren Pip-Summen auf null enden – das macht das Kopfrechnen leicht. Zusammen mit ein paar Key Points und Spiegelmustern decken sie die allermeisten Stellungen ab, die dir begegnen."
          }
        },
        "en": {
          "stringUnit": {
            "state": "translated",
            "value": "Cluster Counting is a technique developed by Jack Kissane that lets you estimate pip counts much faster than the traditional point-by-point method. Instead of multiplying every checker individually, you mentally rearrange the checkers into recognizable patterns – clusters – whose pip totals are easy to calculate. With practice, you can count most positions in a few seconds.\n\nThe key insight is simple: any two points that mirror each other across the board add up to 25. Point 1 and point 24, point 6 and point 19, point 12 and point 13 – always 25. Four checkers in mirror positions therefore count 50, regardless of exactly where they sit.\n\nRather than memorizing endless combinations, Kissane identified seven reference positions whose pip totals end in zero – making mental arithmetic easy. Combined with a few key points and mirror patterns, these cover the vast majority of positions you will encounter."
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "cluster.intro.title": {
      "comment": "Pip Count cluster",
      "extractionState": "manual",
      "localizations": {
        "de": {
          "stringUnit": {
            "state": "translated",
            "value": "Was ist Cluster Counting?"
          }
        },
        "en": {
          "stringUnit": {
            "state": "translated",
            "value": "What is Cluster Counting?"
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "cluster.keyPoints.intro": {
      "comment": "Pip Count cluster",
      "extractionState": "manual",
      "localizations": {
        "de": {
          "stringUnit": {
            "state": "translated",
            "value": "Die beiden am häufigsten genutzten Key Points sind der 5-Punkt und der 20-Punkt (der 5-Punkt des Gegners). \nAuch der 10-, 13- und 15-Punkt sind sehr wertvoll.  "
          }
        },
        "en": {
          "stringUnit": {
            "state": "translated",
            "value": "The two key points most often used are the 5-point and the 20-point (opponent's 5-point). \nThe 10-, 13- and 15-points are also quite valuable.  "
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "cluster.kp1.caption": {
      "comment": "Pip Count cluster",
      "extractionState": "manual",
      "localizations": {
        "de": {
          "stringUnit": {
            "state": "translated",
            "value": "Den 5-Punkt als Key Point nutzen"
          }
        },
        "en": {
          "stringUnit": {
            "state": "translated",
            "value": "Using 5-Point as Key Point"
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "cluster.kp1.explanation": {
      "comment": "Pip Count cluster",
      "extractionState": "manual",
      "localizations": {
        "de": {
          "stringUnit": {
            "state": "translated",
            "value": "Diese Stellung zeigt zwei Beispiele, wie man ein Cluster aus acht Steinen auf einmal zählt, als wären es acht 5er = 40.\n\nSpieler = 40. Gegner = 40."
          }
        },
        "en": {
          "stringUnit": {
            "state": "translated",
            "value": "This position shows two examples of counting a cluster of eight checkers all at once as if they were eight 5's = 40.\n\nPlayer = 40. Opponent = 40."
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "cluster.kp2.caption": {
      "comment": "Pip Count cluster",
      "extractionState": "manual",
      "localizations": {
        "de": {
          "stringUnit": {
            "state": "translated",
            "value": "Den 20-Punkt als Key Point nutzen"
          }
        },
        "en": {
          "stringUnit": {
            "state": "translated",
            "value": "Using 20-Point as Key Point"
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "cluster.kp2.explanation": {
      "comment": "Pip Count cluster",
      "extractionState": "manual",
      "localizations": {
        "de": {
          "stringUnit": {
            "state": "translated",
            "value": "Der 20-Punkt (der 5-Punkt des Gegners) ist der nützlichste Key Point. Alle Steine im Heimfeld deines Gegners sollten als 20 plus die Pips gezählt werden, die nötig sind, um zum 20-Punkt zu gelangen.\n\nDer Count des Spielers ist 108, was sich als fünf 20er + 4 (je zwei vom 22-Punkt zum 20-Punkt) + 4 (einer vom 24-Punkt zum 20-Punkt) vorstellen lässt.\n\nDer Count des Gegners ist 89, vorgestellt als vier 20er + 4 + 5 (für den Stein auf der Bar)."
          }
        },
        "en": {
          "stringUnit": {
            "state": "translated",
            "value": "The 20-point (opponent's 5-point) is the most useful key point. All checkers in your opponent's home board should be counted as 20 plus the pips required to get to the 20-point.\n\nPlayer's count is 108 which can be visualized as five 20's + 4 (two each from the 22-point to the 20-point) + 4 (one from 24-point to 20-point).\n\nOpponent's count is 89, visualized as four 20's + 4 + 5 (for the checker on the bar)."
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "cluster.mentalShifting.intro": {
      "comment": "Pip Count cluster",
      "extractionState": "manual",
      "localizations": {
        "de": {
          "stringUnit": {
            "state": "translated",
            "value": "Es wäre schön, wenn das Brett jedes Mal, wenn du einen Pip Count brauchst, aus Clustern wie den zuvor beschriebenen bestünde. Leider ist das nicht so. Zum Glück lassen sich diese leicht zählbaren Cluster relativ einfach bilden, indem du die Steine gedanklich dorthin verschiebst, wo du sie haben willst. "
          }
        },
        "en": {
          "stringUnit": {
            "state": "translated",
            "value": "It would be nice if every time you needed a pip count, the board would consist of clusters as previously described. Unfortunately, that doesn't happen. Fortunately, these easy-to-count clusters are relatively simple to form by mentally moving the checkers where you want them. "
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "cluster.mirror1.caption": {
      "comment": "Pip Count cluster",
      "extractionState": "manual",
      "localizations": {
        "de": {
          "stringUnit": {
            "state": "translated",
            "value": "Spiegel - Beispiel 1"
          }
        },
        "en": {
          "stringUnit": {
            "state": "translated",
            "value": "Mirror - Example 1"
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "cluster.mirror1.explanation": {
      "comment": "Pip Count cluster",
      "extractionState": "manual",
      "localizations": {
        "de": {
          "stringUnit": {
            "state": "translated",
            "value": "Player: (20 + 5 = 25) × 2 = 50.\n\nOpponent: (13 + 12 = 25) × 2 = 50.\n\nPlayer = 50. Opponent = 50."
          }
        },
        "en": {
          "stringUnit": {
            "state": "translated",
            "value": "Player: (20 + 5 = 25) × 2 = 50.\n\nOpponent: (13 + 12 = 25) × 2 = 50.\n\nPlayer = 50. Opponent = 50."
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "cluster.mirror2.caption": {
      "comment": "Pip Count cluster",
      "extractionState": "manual",
      "localizations": {
        "de": {
          "stringUnit": {
            "state": "translated",
            "value": "Spiegel - Beispiel 2"
          }
        },
        "en": {
          "stringUnit": {
            "state": "translated",
            "value": "Mirror - Example 2"
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "cluster.mirror2.explanation": {
      "comment": "Pip Count cluster",
      "extractionState": "manual",
      "localizations": {
        "de": {
          "stringUnit": {
            "state": "translated",
            "value": "Player: (23 + 2 = 25) + (24 + 1 = 25) = 50 .\n\nOpponent: (18 + 7 = 25) × 2 = 50.\n\nPlayer = 50. Opponent = 50."
          }
        },
        "en": {
          "stringUnit": {
            "state": "translated",
            "value": "Player: (23 + 2 = 25) + (24 + 1 = 25) = 50 .\n\nOpponent: (18 + 7 = 25) × 2 = 50.\n\nPlayer = 50. Opponent = 50."
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "cluster.mirrors.intro": {
      "comment": "Pip Count cluster",
      "extractionState": "manual",
      "localizations": {
        "de": {
          "stringUnit": {
            "state": "translated",
            "value": "Spiegel sind ein weiteres wichtiges Zählwerkzeug. Jeder Punkt auf dem Brett plus sein gespiegelter Gegenpunkt ergibt 25.\nZum Beispiel ergeben 5-Punkt + 20-Punkt, 1-Punkt + 24-Punkt und 12-Punkt + 13-Punkt jeweils 25 Pips. Daraus folgt, dass ein Cluster aus 4 Steinen in Spiegelpositionen insgesamt 50 ergibt. "
          }
        },
        "en": {
          "stringUnit": {
            "state": "translated",
            "value": "Mirrors are another important counting tool. Any point on the board plus its mirror-opposite point equals 25.\nFor example, the 5-point + 20-point, the 1-point + 24-point, and the 12-point + 13-point all total 25 pips. It follows that any cluster of 4 checkers in mirror positions total 50. "
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "cluster.oneWayShift.conclusion": {
      "comment": "Pip Count cluster",
      "extractionState": "manual",
      "localizations": {
        "de": {
          "stringUnit": {
            "state": "translated",
            "value": "Beachte, dass zwei gegnerische Steine auf den 5-Punkt des Gegners verschoben wurden, der von den Steinen des Spielers besetzt ist. Beim Verschieben der Steine eines Spielers kann die Steinposition des anderen Spielers ignoriert werden. "
          }
        },
        "en": {
          "stringUnit": {
            "state": "translated",
            "value": "Note that two of opponent's checkers were shifted to opponent's 5-point which is occupied by player's checkers. When shifting one player's checkers, the other player's checker position can be ignored. "
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "cluster.oneWayShift.intro": {
      "comment": "Pip Count cluster",
      "extractionState": "manual",
      "localizations": {
        "de": {
          "stringUnit": {
            "state": "translated",
            "value": "Beim einseitigen gedanklichen Verschieben bewegst du die Steine vorwärts auf Key Points oder Referenzpositionen und addierst dann die Vorwärtsbewegung zum Wert der Key Points oder Referenzpositionen. "
          }
        },
        "en": {
          "stringUnit": {
            "state": "translated",
            "value": "One-way mental shifting involves moving the checkers forward to key points or reference positions and then adding the forward movement to the value of the key points or reference positions. "
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "cluster.rp1.caption": {
      "comment": "Pip Count cluster",
      "extractionState": "manual",
      "localizations": {
        "de": {
          "stringUnit": {
            "state": "translated",
            "value": "Referenzposition 1:  5-Prime"
          }
        },
        "en": {
          "stringUnit": {
            "state": "translated",
            "value": "Reference Position 1:  5-Prime"
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "cluster.rp1.explanation": {
      "comment": "Pip Count cluster",
      "extractionState": "manual",
      "localizations": {
        "de": {
          "stringUnit": {
            "state": "translated",
            "value": "Multipliziere den Mittelpunkt eines beliebigen 5-Prime mit 10 und du hast gerade ein Cluster aus zehn Steinen gezählt.\nDiese Stellung zeigt ein 5-Prime vom 4-Punkt bis zum 8-Punkt.\nDer 6-Punkt ist der Mittelpunkt, und der Count für diese zehn Steine = 60 Pips (6 × 10). Das ist so, weil sich 5er und 7er zu 6ern mitteln und sich auch 4er und 8er zu 6ern mitteln.\n\nPip Count = 60."
          }
        },
        "en": {
          "stringUnit": {
            "state": "translated",
            "value": "Multiply the midpoint of any 5-prime by 10 and you have just counted a cluster of ten checkers.\nThis position shows a 5-prime from the 4-point to the 8-point.\nThe 6-point is the midpoint and the count for these ten checkers = 60 pips (6 × 10). This is so because 5's and 7's average out to 6's, and 4's and 8's also average out to 6's.\n\nPipCount = 60."
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "cluster.rp2.caption": {
      "comment": "Pip Count cluster",
      "extractionState": "manual",
      "localizations": {
        "de": {
          "stringUnit": {
            "state": "translated",
            "value": "Referenzposition 2:  Geschlossenes Board"
          }
        },
        "en": {
          "stringUnit": {
            "state": "translated",
            "value": "Reference Position 2:  Closed Board"
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "cluster.rp2.explanation": {
      "comment": "Pip Count cluster",
      "extractionState": "manual",
      "localizations": {
        "de": {
          "stringUnit": {
            "state": "translated",
            "value": "Das ist einfach ein 5-Prime um den 4-Punkt plus zwei Steine auf dem Ass-Punkt.\n\nPip Count = 42."
          }
        },
        "en": {
          "stringUnit": {
            "state": "translated",
            "value": "This is just a 5-prime around the 4-point plus two checkers on the ace point.\n\nPipCount = 42."
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "cluster.rp3.caption": {
      "comment": "Pip Count cluster",
      "extractionState": "manual",
      "localizations": {
        "de": {
          "stringUnit": {
            "state": "translated",
            "value": "Referenzposition 3"
          }
        },
        "en": {
          "stringUnit": {
            "state": "translated",
            "value": "Reference Position 3"
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "cluster.rp3.explanation": {
      "comment": "Pip Count cluster",
      "extractionState": "manual",
      "localizations": {
